Emergency services rushed to the scene to assist. The road closed northbound between J31 and J32, near Preston. Northbound traffic is being diverted by National Highways via the solid triangle diversion symbol. The following diversion route is in place: The service said in a statement: "If this closure impacts on your planned route, please allow extra journey time. "Plan ahead, you may wish to re-route or even delay your journey." A spokesperson for National Highways said: "The M6 in Lancashire is closed northbound between J31 and J32 near Preston due to a collision involving a motorcycle. "Emergency Services including Lancashire Police are currently on scene. National Highways Traffic Officers are also on scene assisting with traffic management." More to follow...